.TH CHEATSHEET 1 "2026-06-02" "sway dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cheatsheet \- fullscreen Sway keybinding & skills help overlay (Super+/)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B toggle-cheatsheet.sh
.PP
Bound to
.B $mod+slash
(Super+/) in the default sway mode. Toggles a fullscreen, read-only
.BR eww (1)
overlay. Accepts no arguments.
.SH DESCRIPTION
A three-column reference grid that floats over the whole screen. It is a
.I static,
hand-curated cheat sheet \(em not generated from the live config \(em laid
out in three Pango-markup columns:
.IP \(bu 3
.B Left
\(em Sway window-manager keybindings: Essentials, Window Layouts,
Navigation, Workspaces, Modes, Scratchpad.
.IP \(bu 3
.B Middle
\(em a bookmark of the operator's custom Claude Code skill plugins, plus a
"+ terceros" line for third-party skills. Ends in a pinned, glowing
\(lqSwap Windows\(rq badge \(em the swap-mode binding, surfaced for findability.
.IP \(bu 3
.B Right
\(em tools and scripts, tmux bindings, clipboard, audio/brightness,
display/scaling, and system-settings reminders.
.PP
Each column lives in its own
.I .pango
file and scrolls independently with the mouse wheel. Press
.B Super+/
again \(em or click anywhere on the overlay \(em to dismiss.
.PP
Two complementary help surfaces exist. This overlay
.RB ( Super+/ )
is the curated, color-grouped, at-a-glance grid. The other,
.B $mod+question
.RB ( Super+? ),
runs
.I command-finder.sh
which
.I dynamically
scrapes every
.B ## Action // Description ##
annotated
.B $bindsym
out of the sway config into a searchable rofi list \(em always current,
never hand-edited. Use
.B Super+?
to discover a binding; use
.B Super+/
for the curated overview.
.SH KEYBINDING
.TP
.B $mod+slash
Toggle the overlay. Defined in
.IR ~/.config/sway/modes/default ,
dispatched to
.IR ~/.config/sway/scripts/toggle-cheatsheet.sh ,
which runs
.BR "eww open cheatsheet --toggle" .
.TP
.B $mod+question
The companion dynamic finder (see DESCRIPTION), dispatched via
.B $help
to
.IR ~/.config/sway/scripts/command-finder.sh .
.SH CONTENT MECHANISM
.B cheatsheet.yuck
declares three
.B defpoll
variables \(em
.IR cs-left ", " cs-mid ", " cs-right " \(em"
each running
.RB "" "cat" " of its"
.I .pango
file with
.BR ":interval \(dq999h\(dq" .
The fullscreen
.B defwindow
.RI ( :stacking " overlay, " :focusable " false, " "100% x 100%" )
renders them as three scrollable
.B :markup
labels separated by dividers. The 999h interval means the files are read
essentially once and then cached \(em see GOTCHAS before editing.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/toggle-cheatsheet.sh
Entry point. Sets PATH for the cargo-installed eww and runs
.BR "eww open cheatsheet --toggle" .
.TP
.I ~/.config/eww/widgets/cheatsheet.yuck
eww window + widget. Declares the
.IR cs-left ", " cs-mid ", " cs-right
defpolls and the fullscreen overlay
.BR defwindow .
.TP
.I ~/.config/eww/cheatsheet/cheatsheet-left.pango
Left column \(em Sway WM keybindings.
.TP
.I ~/.config/eww/cheatsheet/cheatsheet-skills.pango
Middle column \(em custom Claude Code skills bookmark.
.TP
.I ~/.config/eww/cheatsheet/cheatsheet-right.pango
Right column \(em tools, tmux, audio, display, system settings.
.TP
.I ~/.config/eww/styles/cheatsheet.scss
Styling \(em the
.B .cs-*
classes (container, header, title, hint, column, divider) and the
translucent dark background.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/modes/default
Defines the
.B $mod+slash
toggle and the
.B $mod+question
finder bindings.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.BR eww (1)
(Wayland build, run under the
.B eww.service
systemd user unit),
Pango markup, and an installed Nerd Font for the section-header glyphs.
.SH GOTCHAS
.TP
.B Edits are not live \(em reload after editing a .pango file
Because the columns load through
.B defpoll
with
.BR ":interval \(dq999h\(dq" ,
editing a
.I .pango
file does NOT update the overlay on its own. Run
.B eww reload
(or
.BR "eww poll cs-left cs-mid cs-right" )
afterwards. Re-opening the overlay alone can still show stale cached text.
.TP
.B eww is systemd-managed
Do not
.B eww kill
/
.BR "eww daemon" .
Use
.B eww reload
for content changes and
.B systemctl --user restart eww.service
for a full restart \(em a manual daemon spawns a second instance and you
get duplicate windows.
.TP
.B Never reload while the overlay is open
Running
.B eww reload
while the cheatsheet is open can leave a stale ghost surface on top that the
toggle no longer tracks \(em trapping the screen (this happened 2026-06-02).
Edit the
.I .pango
files (or this widget) only while it is CLOSED, then reload. Safety nets now
in place:
.B :focusable false
(the window cannot grab the keyboard, so
.B Super+/
always toggles it off), clicking anywhere closes it, and
.B "eww close cheatsheet"
from a TTY is the last resort.
.TP
.B Nerd Font PUA glyphs in the .pango files
The section headers use Private-Use-Area glyphs that are invisible to
text-processing tools and can be silently dropped by a naive full rewrite.
Edit the files with byte-preserving, surgical edits \(em never blind-overwrite.
.TP
.B Manual curation drifts
Unlike
.B Super+?
(command-finder, auto-generated), this overlay is hand-maintained and
.I will
go stale as keybindings change. Re-sync it against
.I ~/.config/sway/modes/*
and the installed skill set periodically.
.TP
.B Column alignment is space-padded
Each label is left-padded to a fixed monospace width before its value
.RB ( <span> ) \(em
roughly 25 chars in the left/right columns, 21 (after the leading emoji) in
the skills column. Preserve the padding or the columns misalign.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR eww (1),
.BR sway (5),
.BR palette-theming (1)
.PP
Companion dynamic finder:
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/command-finder.sh
.RB ( $mod+question ).
